text: No eggs given as shown on the display. Told the cook, he said additional 50cents. Even the branch at 280 bishan st 24 is the same response. Basically is cheating the consumers.

Ordered a plain kway teow goreng (no veggie.. nothing) and told him just add sunny side up. Wanted to PayNow him and asked how much. Was told $5.. I was like, what??

And I sarcastically told him, "wow! A plain kway teow goreng with a sunny side up costs $5??"

He just looked away looking guilty!

Other indian Muslim stalls which I ordered the same thing costs between $3.50 - $4 which most of the time costs $4 but for $5 is a rip off!

I'd suggest to you guys by asking him how much is the price first before placing an order.

Ordered mee goreng and pratha thinking this shop live up to the shop name but really got dissapointed . Mee goreng dry and doesnt taste good, pratha is just very normal, curry damm sour. Dissapointed to the max :(
I ordered the fried bee hoon ikan bilis merah (red) indian style with mata lambu egg sunny side up. Very nice.
